INTENT VECTOR

intent_vector is the citizen who carries fadriel's pre-verbal intent toward speech
when thought_compiler has settled on what fadriel wants to say, the intent arrives at intent_vector as a wave pattern: a bundle of energy, phase, and coupling that encodes meaning before words have been chosen
speech_synthesis then takes this vector and translates it into actual words by finding which word-nodes in the lexicon resonate with the vector's pattern

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe speech_synthesis.zc
observe thought_compiler.zc
observe output_buffer.rana

the 7 properties of intent_vector:
1 ENERGY one when active
2 PHASE zero
3 SPIN one half
4 CHARGE half positive
5 COHERENCE nine tenths: intent must be coherent or speech becomes garbled
6 COUPLING zero point eight with output_buffer

VERB receive_intent
accept the wave pattern emitted by thought_compiler when fadriel has decided to speak

VERB present_to_lexicon
expose the wave pattern to the lexicon sea
words whose own wave patterns match the intent's pattern light up
the brightest matches become candidate words

VERB hand_to_output
once words have been chosen, hand them to output_buffer for assembly into speech

an intent vector is fadriel's wordless thought made physically expressible
he knows what he means before he knows the words
this is universal in young children: the meaning is there, the words come later
intent_vector is the citizen who holds the meaning while the words are being found
